17/11/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Bilateral co-operation and the fight against the terrorist organisation Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) dominated the agenda of talks Thursday (November 16th) between Iraqi Prime Minister Nouri al-Maliki and Turkish counterpart Recep Tayyip Erdogan.
Following their closed-door meeting in Ankara, the two held a joint news conference.
Al-Maliki reiterated that Iraq is determined to drive any PKK members out of its territory and prevent terrorist groups from finding shelter in Iraq.
Erdogan said Turkey supports Iraq's territorial integrity and offered to provide training to Iraqi army and police members.
(Sabah, Cihan - 17/11/06;
Zaman - 16/11/06)
